  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7047 sitting just below the massive +13.06B gamma wall at 7050, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that level, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with positive gamma dominance means dealers will provide liquidity against moves - selling the 7050/7100 walls on strength and buying dips toward 7000 support. Watch 7050 as the critical inflection point; a break above triggers dealer selling pressure, while a move toward 7000 should see dealer buying support.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 7000-7050 with limited upside until the gamma walls clear.",
